<title>JAPAN: JT shares slip after U.S. settlement.</title>
<headline>JT shares slip after U.S. settlement.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-06-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Japan Tobacco Inc shares slipped on Monday morning following news that the U.S. tobacco industry, health advocates and 40 states suing the industry had reached a $368.5 billion landmark settlement on Friday, brokers said.</p>
<p>As of 0130 GMT, the shares of Japan's tobacco monopoly were down 21,000 yen at 916,000.  </p>
<p>&quot;There is speculation that such a settlement will hasten anti-smoking moves even in Japan, which would be damaging to JT's business,&quot; a trader at a foreign brokerage said. &quot;But trade in the shares is extremely thin, exaggerating the fall, and the weakness will probably be a one-time thing.&quot;</p>
</text>
